result.name: Ootoya

reviews.text:
Originated from Japan.  Most of the meat and fish are imported there. The Japanese chief chef works well to maintain a quality standard as equally good as in Japan. Offers various kind of meal set and a la cart. Lunch and dinner menu are basically the same but there are skewers and sashimi available at dinner time. Price point is not low but very fair for what you get.

Peak hours always got queue and reservation not accepted. So better go ahead or after the crowd.  Ultimately, there are many restaurants in the building as backup. 😅

This is my first time in this shop, usually I go to Kowloon side branch.  There is not much people during 12 o clock noon time, only 4 or 5 tables are occupied.  They do have special price lunch menu.  And they are around 80 dollars.  I have tried the mini size salmon rice and cold soba.  They are come in as a lunch set.  Surprisingly,  the taste is better than the other branches I tried before.  And the place is quite spacious.  I do enjoy my lunch here today.  5 🌟!!!
Good location, good services and good price ~
Good service and the side dishes are the best among all branches, I like this one greatly!
The food was sub par, the air con was broken, the toilet was out of order and the tables were close to.each other. Terrible experience.

Delicious food lovingly prepared. Pleasant service, where nothing is too much trouble. 

One of best 'all you can eat' dinners among Japanese restaurants. High quality ingredients, straightforwardly cooked, always reliable. A bit expensive but actually mid priced, by Japanese restaurant standards.

reviews.text: Roast pork set.  Tad salty but overall very tasty.  Very busy during lunch so best visit earlier.  No reservations available.  Would definitely visit again.

A Japanese restaurant with a long long queue

So if you're looking for a quite lunch. I suggest somewhere else with takeaway Japs food. Their quality is quite good with mains that can come in a set or just the main. So quite some freedom for a leisure lunch. Not too noisy that you can't chat but you can find more quiet around Central.

Good quality & tasty food 
No reservation during lunch time; a long queue daily, have to wait for half an hour

Double the price of Ootoya in Japan but same great Japanese quality and consistency. Very spacious restaurant which is rare for Hong Kong. Satisfied overall. Free beverage for enrolling into their membership.

Was heading to off a different restaurant for lunch and noticed this Japanese chain restaurant on the way so decided to give it a try.  We made a good decision.  Service was great for Hong Kong standard.  Food is good.  Taste exactly like food in Japan.  The grilled mackerel was amazing.  The fish and veggie combo set I had was really good.  Everything was cooked and seasoned perfectly.  Our family of 5 left with a smile on our face.  Will return for more.
